content=["<dl>",
"<dt><a href='#Section0'>Atopic dermatitis</a></dt>",
"<dd id='Section0'>",
"<p><strong>Sign & Symptoms:</strong> Lesions in atopic dermatitis are generally symmetrically distributed over the flexural areas, less likely to be vesicular, more chronic in nature with seasonal variation, and not as sharply delineated.Family history in atopic patients is often positive for atopy.",
"<br><strong>Test:</strong> Patch testing is negative for atopic dermatitis, but may be positive if contact dermatitis and atopic dermatitis co-exist in the same patient.</p>",
"</dd>",
"<dt><a href='#Section1'>Nummular eczema</a></dt>",
"<dd id='Section1'>",
"<p><strong>Sign & Symptoms:</strong> Lesions in nummular eczema are coin-shaped plaques, with pinpoint vesiculation, and symmetrically distributed, most commonly on the extensor lower extremities.",
"<br><strong>Test:</strong> Patch testing is negative in case of nummular eczema.</p>",
"</dd>",
"<dt><a href='#Section2'>Dyshidrotic eczema</a></dt>",
"<dd id='Section2'>",
"<p><strong>Sign & Symptoms:</strong> Dyshidrotic eczema almost exclusively involves the palms and soles, with little to no involvement of the dorsal hands and feet.",
"<br><strong>Test:</strong> Patch testing is negative in cases of dyshidrotic eczema.</p>",
"</dd>",
"</dl>"].join("\n");